The paper deals with the problem of using image queries to retrieve videos from a database, which is a common task in computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) research. The authors propose a framework based on Bloom filters, which is a data structure commonly used in information retrieval (cs.IR) and data storage (cs.DS) applications. The paper also discusses different retrieval architectures and encoding functions, which are relevant to database systems (cs.DB).
